Interface ProxyRecorderPluginInterface

    • Method Detail

      • getDescription

        java.lang.String getDescription()
        Get a short description about the recorder plug-in.
        Returns:
        a short description about the recorder plug-in in plain ASCII format.

      • getExtendedHTMLDescription

        java.lang.String getExtendedHTMLDescription()
        Get an extended description about the recorder plug-in in HTML formatted text. If the plug-in can be called manually and the manual call has arguments then the extended description should also contain information about the meaning of the arguments.
        Returns:
        the extended description about the recorder plug-in as HTML formatted text, or null if no extended description shall be displayed.

      • isDefaultActive

        boolean isDefaultActive()
        Get if the recorder plug-in is active by default (active = called by the proxy recorder during recording a session). Note: if the plug-in allows manual calls only then it will remain always in inactive state, even if this method return true.
        Returns:
        true if the recorder plug-in is active by default. Note: inactive plug-ins can be activated later by using the Web Admin GUI or the REST API.
        See Also:
        stopRecording(ProxyRecorderContext), stopRecording(ProxyRecorderContext), clearRecording(ProxyRecorderContext), beforeURLTransmitToServer(ProxyRecorderContext, ProxyRecorderPluginURLContext), afterURLReceiveFromServer(ProxyRecorderContext, ProxyRecorderPluginURLContext), allowManualCallOnly()

      • getExecutionPosition

        int getExecutionPosition()
        Get a hint about the execution order if multiple active recorder plug-ins are defined. Note: plug-ins with the highest execution position are executed at first for HTTP requests and at last for HTTP responses. If the plug-in method allowManualCallOnly() returns true then the execution order is never used.
        Returns:
        a hint about the execution order if multiple active recorder plug-ins are defined (can also be a non-unique number)
        See Also:
        allowManualCallOnly()

      • allowManualCall

        boolean allowManualCall()
        Get if it's allowed to call the plug-in manually by using the Web Admin GUI or the REST API.
        Returns:
        true = it's allowed to call the plug-in manually
        See Also:
        getManualCallArgumentDescriptors(), manualCall(ProxyRecorderContext, String[])

      • allowManualCallOnly

        boolean allowManualCallOnly()
        Get if the plug-in can be called manually only by using the Web Admin GUI or the REST API. If this method return true then the plug-in remains always in inactive state and cannot be activated.
        Returns:
        true = if the plug-in can be called manually only
        See Also:
        getManualCallArgumentDescriptors(), manualCall(ProxyRecorderContext, String[])

      • getManualCallArgumentDescriptors

        ProxyRecorderPluginArgumentDescriptor[] getManualCallArgumentDescriptors()
        Get the label text(s) and the default value(s) of the arguments when the plug-in is manually called by using the Web Admin GUI or the REST API.
        Returns:
        the label text(s) and the default value(s) in plain ASCII format of the arguments. Derived from this return information also the number of arguments is implicitly set. You can also return null or an empty array if no arguments are needed when calling the plug-in manually.
        See Also:
        getManualCallArgumentDescriptors(), allowManualCall(), manualCall(ProxyRecorderContext, String[])

      • manualCall

        void manualCall(ProxyRecorderContext recorderContext,
              java.lang.String[] arguments)
        The plug-in is called manually by using the Web Admin GUI or the REST API.
        Parameters:
        recorderContext - context of the proxy recorder
        arguments - the arguments passed from the caller (Web Admin GUI or REST API)
        See Also:
        allowManualCall(), getManualCallArgumentDescriptors()

      • activeChange

        void activeChange(ProxyRecorderContext recorderContext,
                boolean isActive)
        Called when the plug-in changes its active state.
        Parameters:
        recorderContext - context of the proxy recorder
        isActive - true = the plug-in was inactive and is now active, false = the plug-in was active and is now inactive
